Note on agent design:
These reference agents call the customer's own Claude Agent SDK instance for
LLM reasoning. The jpcite operator (Bookyou株式会社) does NOT proxy LLM calls
and does NOT charge for LLM tokens. Customers pay Anthropic directly for
Claude usage and pay jpcite ¥3/req for the underlying data API.

Note on data license:
The agent code is MIT-licensed. Program metadata returned by the jpcite REST /
MCP API is aggregated from Japanese government primary sources and is governed
by Bookyou株式会社's terms (https://jpcite.com/tos.html).
